						<summary>

						<p>A broken pillar lying in the compound of the Siddhēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 12th century, on the basis of internal evidence.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. It seems to record an endowment of some <hi rend="italic">Vṛittis</hi> of land after purchase by Kannaya and Mallaya for 100 <hi rend="italic">gadyāṇas.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
